JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates FC have been found guilty of contravening rule 54 of the National Soccer League Handbook. This after acts of hooliganism by a section of supporters during the Absa Premiership fixture against Mamelodi Sundowns on 11 February 2017, at which fans invaded the pitch. The Premier Soccer LeagueÂ disciplinary committee is expected to reconvene in 2018 to impose sanctions on the club. The case against Mamelodi Sundowns will be considered in January. eNCA